      <description>&lt;h1 id=&#34;clean-code-list&#34;&gt;Clean Code List&lt;/h1&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://smalldata.tech/blog/2018/09/16/clean-code-notes&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;CLEAN CODE - NOTES&lt;/a&gt;: The following is a list of notes taken on writing clean code, i.e. code that is maintainable and extensible.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://tech.meituan.com/clean-code.html&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;美团点评技术团队 - 聊聊 clean code&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://hackernoon.com/software-complexity-naming-6e02e7e6c8cb&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;Software Complexity: The Art of Naming&lt;/a&gt;: There are only two hard things in Computer Science: cache invalidation and naming things.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;http://www.techug.com/anti-if-the-missing-patterns&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;编程时避免使用 if 语句的五种模式&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://hackernoon.com/you-might-not-need-if-statements-a-better-approach-to-branching-logic-59b4f877697f#.pnmxdconp&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;You might not need if statements: a better approach to branching logic&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&#34;https://zhuanlan.zhihu.com/p/24543157&#34; target=&#34;_blank&#34; rel=&#34;noopener&#34;&gt;如何跟老代码友好相处&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
